

GOAL: Add a map intent to a button located inside in listview
OBSTACLES:
- prevent the button from being included in onItemClick for the rest of the item view
	- SOLUTION: add android:descendantFocusability="blocksDescendants" to item_view layout 
	
- add onClickListener to the button
	- SOLUTION: In custom adapter, create ImageView object for the button and set onClickListener
	 
- cannot resolve startActivity in onClickListener
	- SOLUTION: add getContext() method in front of startActivity method.
	
- create map intent to show directions from current location to destination
	- SOLUTION: 
		- parse "google.navigation:q=" + current item coordinates getter method to set destination in Google maps

SOLUTION:
ImageView button = (ImageView) listItemView.findViewById(R.id.go_button);
        button.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                Intent mapIntent = new Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW, Uri.parse("google.navigation:q=" + currentItem.getmCoordinates()));
                getContext().startActivity(mapIntent);
            }
        });

